      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Gelar Sang Penguasa Setara Langit',
        headingEn: 'The Title of Great Sage Equal to Heaven',
        body: '''Murka atas ulah Wukong, para raja naga dan Yan Wang mengadukannya kepada Kaisar Giok. Atas saran salah seorang penasihat, Kaisar Giok memilih meredamnya dengan tipu daya lembut: Wukong dipanggil ke Surga dan diangkat menjadi Bimawen, pengurus kuda istal langit. Wukong bekerja penuh semangat hingga suatu hari ia bertanya tentang pangkatnya dan mengetahui bahwa jabatan itu adalah yang paling hina di seluruh birokrasi Surga, tanpa gelar maupun kehormatan. Terhina, ia membalikkan meja perjamuan, menghancurkan istal, dan turun kembali ke Gunung Bunga-Buah, memasang panji bertuliskan "Qitian Dasheng", Sang Penguasa Setara Langit. Kaisar Giok mengirim pasukan pimpinan Li Jing dan putranya Nezha untuk menangkapnya, namun keduanya dikalahkan telak. Alih-alih terus berperang, atas saran Dewa Bintang Panjang Usia (Taibai Jinxing), Kaisar Giok memilih jalan damai dan benar-benar menganugerahkan gelar Qitian Dasheng kepada Wukong, lengkap dengan sebuah istana kehormatan, demi menjaga ketenteraman Surga meski gelar itu hampa dari kekuasaan sesungguhnya.''',
        bodyEn: '''Enraged by Wukong's deeds, the dragon kings and King Yan complained to the Jade Emperor. On an advisor's suggestion, the Jade Emperor chose to placate him with a gentle ruse: Wukong was summoned to Heaven and appointed Bimawen, keeper of the celestial stables. He worked with great enthusiasm until one day he asked about his rank and learned the post was the lowest in the entire Heavenly bureaucracy, carrying no title or honor whatsoever. Humiliated, he overturned the banquet table, wrecked the stables, and returned to Flower-Fruit Mountain, raising a banner proclaiming himself "Qitian Dasheng," the Great Sage Equal to Heaven. The Jade Emperor sent an army led by Li Jing and his son Nezha to capture him, but both were soundly defeated. Rather than continue fighting, on the advice of the Star of Longevity, Taibai Jinxing, the Jade Emperor chose the path of peace and formally granted Wukong the title of Great Sage Equal to Heaven, complete with an honorary palace, to preserve Heaven's peace even though the title carried no real power.''',
