        headingEn: 'Chaos at the Feast of Immortal Peaches',
        body: '''Untuk menyibukkannya, para dewa menugaskan Wukong menjaga Taman Persik Keabadian milik Ratu Xi Wangmu, tempat pohon-pohon persik ajaib berbuah sekali setiap tiga ribu, enam ribu, dan sembilan ribu tahun, masing-masing memberi umur panjang, keabadian tubuh, atau kesetaraan dengan langit dan bumi bagi siapa pun yang memakannya. Tergoda, Wukong diam-diam memakan hampir seluruh persik matang di taman itu. Ketika bidadari-bidadari datang memetik buah untuk Pesta Persik tahunan, yang mengundang seluruh dewa penting termasuk Buddha dan para dewa abadi, mereka mendapati taman itu nyaris kosong. Wukong, yang tidak diundang ke pesta karena statusnya yang rendah, murka dan menyusup ke perjamuan, melumpuhkan para penjaga, meminum seluruh anggur langit, dan melahap hidangan istimewa. Dalam keadaan mabuk, ia tersesat memasuki istana Laozi, dewa alkimia tertinggi, dan menemukan sebuah labu berisi pil elixir emas hasil tempaan tungku Delapan Trigram selama ribuan tahun. Tanpa ragu, ia menelan seluruh isi labu itu, menggandakan kekuatan sihirnya hingga hampir tak terkalahkan.''',
        bodyEn: '''To keep him occupied, the gods assigned Wukong to guard the Garden of Immortal Peaches belonging to Queen Mother Xi Wangmu, where the magical peach trees bore fruit once every three thousand, six thousand, and nine thousand years, each granting long life, bodily immortality, or equality with heaven and earth to whoever ate them. Tempted, Wukong secretly devoured nearly every ripe peach in the garden. When celestial maidens arrived to gather fruit for the annual Peach Banquet, which would host every important deity including the Buddha and the immortals, they found the garden nearly bare. Wukong, uninvited to the feast due to his low status, flew into a rage and slipped into the banquet, disabling the guards, drinking all the heavenly wine, and devouring the finest delicacies. In his drunken stupor, he wandered into the palace of Laozi, the supreme god of alchemy, and found a gourd filled with golden elixir pills forged over millennia in his Eight Trigrams Furnace. Without hesitation, he swallowed the entire contents, doubling his magical power until he became nearly unstoppable.''',
