    impact: '''Kejatuhan Guan Yu dan hilangnya Jingzhou menjadi pukulan strategis yang tak pernah pulih sepenuhnya bagi Shu Han, memutus akses penting ke jalur perdagangan dan pertahanan yang telah dibangun bertahun-tahun, serta memicu Pertempuran Yiling yang semakin melemahkan kerajaan itu. Namun dalam jangka panjang, kematiannya justru melahirkan salah satu kultus keagamaan rakyat paling luas dan bertahan lama dalam sejarah Tiongkok. Sebagai Guandi, Guan Yu dipuja lintas agama, oleh umat Tao, Buddha, bahkan Konfusianisme, serta lintas kelas sosial, dari kaisar hingga pedagang jalanan, menjadikannya salah satu simbol pemersatu budaya paling kuat dalam peradaban Tiongkok, dan kuil-kuilnya menjadi pusat komunitas Tionghoa perantauan di seluruh dunia hingga saat ini.''',
    impactEn: '''Guan Yu's downfall and the loss of Jing Province was a strategic blow from which Shu Han never fully recovered, severing crucial access to trade routes and defenses built up over years, and triggering the Battle of Yiling, which further weakened the kingdom. In the long run, however, his death gave rise to one of the most widespread and enduring folk religious cults in Chinese history. As Guandi, Guan Yu is worshipped across religious lines, by Taoists, Buddhists, and even Confucians, and across social classes, from emperors to street merchants, making him one of the most powerful unifying cultural symbols in Chinese civilization, with his temples serving as community centers for overseas Chinese communities worldwide to this day.''',
    meaning: '''Kisah kematian Guan Yu menjadi meditasi mendalam tentang harga kesetiaan mutlak dan bahaya kesombongan di puncak kejayaan. Kemenangannya yang gemilang di Fancheng, yang seharusnya menjadi puncak kariernya, justru menjadi awal kejatuhannya karena ia meremehkan ancaman dari Sun Quan yang dianggapnya sekutu lemah. Namun keteguhannya menolak menyerah bahkan di ambang maut mengangkatnya menjadi teladan yi, kesetiaan dan kebenaran moral, salah satu nilai tertinggi dalam etika Konfusianisme. Transformasinya dari manusia fana menjadi dewa menegaskan kepercayaan Tiongkok bahwa kebajikan luar biasa, terutama kesetiaan tanpa syarat, dapat mengangkat seseorang melampaui batas kematian menuju keabadian ilahi.''',
    meaningEn: '''The story of Guan Yu's death is a profound meditation on the cost of absolute loyalty and the dangers of pride at the height of glory. His brilliant victory at Fancheng, which should have marked the pinnacle of his career, instead became the beginning of his downfall, as he underestimated the threat from Sun Quan, whom he dismissed as a weak ally. Yet his steadfast refusal to surrender even at the brink of death elevated him into a model of yi, loyalty and moral righteousness, one of the highest values in Confucian ethics. His transformation from mortal man into god affirms the Chinese belief that extraordinary virtue, especially unconditional loyalty, can raise a person beyond the bounds of death into divine eternity.''',
